1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,500
I haven't seen you in ages, Marcus.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,800
You look like you've been through hell.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,000
Tell your sister to break a leg
before the show tonight.

4
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,200
I'll meet you by the bank at noon.
Bring the documents.

5
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:16,500
No, not the river bank —
the one on Fifth Avenue.

6
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,800
Oh, great. Just great.

7
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:21,500
Relax, this'll be a piece of cake.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
It's raining cats and dogs out there.
Did you bring an umbrella?

9
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,500
The server is down. We need to reboot
the firewall before the meeting.

10
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
I'll grab a coffee at Starbucks
and meet you at Penn Station.

11
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,500
We have a mole in the department.
Someone's been leaking information.

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
The suspect said they would cooperate,
but their lawyer disagreed.

13
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,800
Take the light bag, not the heavy one.

14
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:45,500
Your Honor, my client, Mr. O'Brien,
has cooperated fully.

15
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,500
I <i>knew</i> you'd come through, kid.

16
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,200
Don't get cold feet now.

17
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:55,000
If anyone asks, you were never here.
Understood?

18
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:58,500
We need 10 milligrams of adrenaline,
stat!

19
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Damn it, Marcus!

20
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:05,000
Whatever happens tonight...
remember, I've always had your back.
